WEBVTT

00:50.718 --> 00:52.629
Another secret identity, Mr. Teague?

00:54.805 --> 00:56.090
Excuse me?

00:57.975 --> 01:01.809
Why is it that when people are in trouble
they run to South America?

01:03.063 --> 01:07.477
Young lady, when I chartered this jet,
I was promised a discreet journey.

01:07.651 --> 01:09.812
I'm not interested
in having a conversation.

01:12.156 --> 01:14.818
I'm not big on small talk either.

01:15.534 --> 01:18.492
I'd rather hear about Veritas.

01:20.205 --> 01:21.945
Who are you?

01:24.126 --> 01:26.663
Someone that knows the Traveler...

01:26.837 --> 01:29.579
...and that you tried to destroy him.

01:29.757 --> 01:32.419
l have no idea what you're talking about.

01:37.556 --> 01:39.046
You know...

01:39.224 --> 01:42.967
...for the last surviving member
of a secret society...

01:43.145 --> 01:44.635
...you're not a very good liar.

01:50.486 --> 01:51.851
[TEAGUE GRUNTS]

01:52.946 --> 01:56.188
The device that controls the Traveler,
where is it?

01:56.366 --> 01:58.027
Let me go.

02:06.210 --> 02:07.791
[TEAGUE GASPS]

02:07.961 --> 02:11.294
We're 20,000 feet up, Mr. Teague.
Tell me where the device is...

02:11.465 --> 02:13.501
...or you'll start your descent early.

02:13.675 --> 02:15.211
What the hell are you doing?

02:20.724 --> 02:22.339
One last chance.

02:22.518 --> 02:24.509
Tell me where the device is.

02:25.312 --> 02:26.643
Lex Luthor.

02:26.814 --> 02:29.726
He might have the answers
you're looking for.

02:31.777 --> 02:34.314
Enjoy the rest of your ﬂight.

03:49.396 --> 03:50.727
[DOOR OPENS]

03:51.523 --> 03:52.729
REGAN:
Mr. Luthor.

03:52.900 --> 03:55.312
Has the team reached the target?

03:56.320 --> 03:58.151
We lost contact an hour ago.

03:58.322 --> 04:01.359
They may have run into a bad patch
of weather, some interference.

04:01.533 --> 04:03.910
The satellite shows clear skies
over the Arctic.

04:04.077 --> 04:06.819
They were less than 10 miles away
when the signal cutout.

04:06.997 --> 04:11.081
We tried to get a visual, but there's no sign
of them. Just like the last team.

04:11.251 --> 04:15.164
I thought the Bermuda Triangle
was somewhere a little more tropical.

04:15.672 --> 04:18.459
People don't just vanish off
the face of the planet.

04:18.634 --> 04:20.090
Find them.

04:25.849 --> 04:28.181
Sorry. Hey, boss.

04:28.352 --> 04:30.809
If this is about my article proposal,
I got an idea:

04:30.979 --> 04:33.721
A two-page spread of color glossies
from the Kiwatche caves.

04:33.899 --> 04:36.686
It'll make National Geographic
look like a travel brochure.

04:36.860 --> 04:39.021
We'll talk about your proposal later.

04:39.196 --> 04:41.653
Oh. Okay.

04:41.823 --> 04:44.530
My phone call
to the Department of Domestic Security...

04:44.701 --> 04:47.363
...kept Chloe out of federal prison.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.695
Now I need your help.

04:51.333 --> 04:52.493
What do you need?

04:53.210 --> 04:55.872
Lois Lane off my back.

04:56.171 --> 04:59.880
She's been asking too many people
too many questions.

05:00.133 --> 05:03.000
What can I do?
Lois isn't exactly a pushover.

05:03.178 --> 05:05.260
It's impossible to break her press power.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.466
I'm well aware of your limitations.

05:07.641 --> 05:09.848
Just help her ﬁnd some information.

05:17.567 --> 05:19.353
Is any of this true?

05:19.736 --> 05:21.897
What matters is you make her believe
it's true.

05:24.241 --> 05:25.651
So you want me to lie?

05:25.826 --> 05:27.566
I want you to do whatever it takes.

05:27.911 --> 05:30.573
-Oh.... Lex.
-Jimmy.

05:31.748 --> 05:37.209
It would be tragic if the DDS decided Chloe
was a threat to national security after all.

05:46.096 --> 05:48.087
[DOORBELL RINGING]

05:49.016 --> 05:50.347
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

05:51.351 --> 05:52.431
5:33.23;
a. Q._:
g§Q-@:
%%

05:52.602 --> 05:55.969
Get the lead out, Smallville.
Opportunity is knocking on your door.

05:56.148 --> 05:57.228
Come on in, Lois.

05:57.399 --> 06:00.607
Big news. An intern just got promoted
to Chloe's old desk.

06:00.777 --> 06:03.063
I'm happy that someone took
my best friend's job?

06:03.238 --> 06:06.526
Absolutely, because it opens up a spot
in the bullpen.

06:06.700 --> 06:09.237
And guess whose name
is written all over it.

06:09.953 --> 06:11.864
Clark Kent.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.280
Got your application right here.

06:15.959 --> 06:18.075
That's never gonna happen.

06:18.503 --> 06:21.791
Now if you would excuse me,
l have chores to do.

06:21.965 --> 06:25.833
Seriously, Clark, don't you think
you're destined for greater things in life...

06:26.011 --> 06:28.172
...than working on a farm?

06:28.513 --> 06:31.471
Even if I wanted the job, Lois,
I'd never work for Lex Luthor.

06:31.641 --> 06:32.892
[LOIS SIGHS]

06:34.269 --> 06:37.636
Okay. Then why were you
such great friends with the guy?

06:37.814 --> 06:41.477
Looking into Lex's past,
I found out just how far you two go back.

06:44.362 --> 06:46.318
You're nothing alike.

06:46.490 --> 06:48.481
Why were you so close for so long?

06:49.576 --> 06:53.819
Sometimes, people don't turn out to be
what you thought they were.

06:55.332 --> 06:59.450
Lois, if you're gonna continue working
for Lex, promise me you'll be careful.

06:59.920 --> 07:00.955
[SCOFFS]

07:01.129 --> 07:04.838
If I didn't know any better, Smallville,
I'd think you were worried about me.

07:08.261 --> 07:09.592
[DOOR OPENS]

07:10.138 --> 07:11.423
Hey, Lois.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.089
Can I talk to Clark for a second?

07:15.393 --> 07:17.725
Yeah, I think we're done here.

07:18.063 --> 07:20.179
Just think about your future, okay?

07:25.821 --> 07:28.938
So a private jet just went down
over upstate New York.

07:29.116 --> 07:33.029
Three bodies were recovered
and one was identiﬁed...

07:33.203 --> 07:34.784
...as Edward Teague.

07:39.334 --> 07:41.325
CHLOE:
I used every skill in my arsenal.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.368
Once I found out
about the plane crash...

07:43.547 --> 07:45.913
...I made my way
into the NTSB mainframe.

07:46.091 --> 07:49.083
According to the ﬂight plan,
they were on their way to Buenos Aires.

07:49.261 --> 07:50.671
They were in the air an hour...

07:50.846 --> 07:53.428
...when something shot out
of the cabin like a missile.

07:53.598 --> 07:55.213
What do you mean, shot out?

07:55.392 --> 07:56.882
The copilot went to the back...

07:57.060 --> 08:00.223
...to ﬁnd out what was going on
and he was knocked unconscious.

08:00.397 --> 08:02.433
-Do they have any idea what it was?
-No.

08:02.607 --> 08:06.896
They found the black box
and I was able to download this audio.

08:08.238 --> 08:11.355
PILOT [ON RECORDING]: Something's wrong.
Felt like a collision in the cabin.

08:11.533 --> 08:14.366
We 're losing air pressure.
l'rn going back to take a look.

08:14.703 --> 08:16.614
What the hell are you doing?

08:16.788 --> 08:18.324
[PILOT GRUNTS]

08:20.125 --> 08:21.581
After that it's all garbled.

08:21.751 --> 08:26.745
I tried running it through the ﬁlter a dozen
times but I could only come up with noise.

08:27.591 --> 08:29.252
Play it again.

08:38.935 --> 08:41.017
KARA [ON RECORDING]:
We're 20, 000 feet up, Mr. Teague.

08:41.188 --> 08:42.724
Tell me where the device is...

08:42.898 --> 08:46.186
...or you'll be starting your descent
earlier than expected.

08:47.402 --> 08:49.643
-Kara.
-Kara?

08:49.821 --> 08:52.107
What's she doing with Edward Teague?

08:52.282 --> 08:53.488
I don't know.

08:53.658 --> 08:56.525
But I just heard her threaten
to bring the plane down.

08:58.121 --> 09:01.033
We both know how reckless she can be
when she's angry.

09:01.208 --> 09:03.665
Maybe she found out
that Teague was after you again.

09:03.835 --> 09:07.453
There must be some other explanation,
Chloe. She's not a killer.

09:07.631 --> 09:10.498
Look, Clark, I'm a fan of Kara's as well...

09:10.675 --> 09:15.214
...but unless you're hearing things,
it sounds like she caused that accident.

09:15.472 --> 09:17.679
Remember what you said
when she ﬁrst got here?

09:17.849 --> 09:21.467
Just about every Kryptonian you've met
turned out to be a cold-blooded killer.

09:21.645 --> 09:22.976
I know her.

09:23.146 --> 09:25.057
She's my cousin.

09:26.066 --> 09:28.057
She's not a killer.

09:30.195 --> 09:31.901
I just need to ﬁnd her.

09:32.781 --> 09:34.897
Is there any more audio?

09:35.075 --> 09:36.815
There's a little more noise.

09:36.993 --> 09:38.324
[STATIC CRACKLING]

09:39.329 --> 09:41.661
[TEAGUE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

09:44.417 --> 09:46.123
What is it?

09:46.336 --> 09:48.543
She's going after Lex.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.015
What are you doing here, Kara?

10:48.106 --> 10:49.971
Trying to protect you.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.186
By threatening to kill Edward Teague?

10:52.360 --> 10:55.067
I heard the recording.
Those men are dead.

10:55.613 --> 10:58.741
Tell me you're not responsible
for their plane going down.

10:59.743 --> 11:01.358
It's Teague's fault.

11:01.536 --> 11:05.120
If he hadn't gone after the Traveler,
he'd still be alive.

11:06.666 --> 11:07.746
We need to talk.

11:11.379 --> 11:13.870
-Let go of me.
-Kara, I've been worried about you...

11:14.549 --> 11:17.416
...but I guess I should have been worried
about everyone else.

11:18.428 --> 11:20.168
Have you come into contact
with Red Kryptonite?

11:20.347 --> 11:22.429
-Ring, necklace--?
-Stopped wearing jewelry.

11:22.599 --> 11:25.511
Then something must have happened
when you went back to Krypton.

11:26.603 --> 11:28.264
Do you remember anything strange?

11:28.438 --> 11:29.553
I'm ﬁne, Kal-El.

11:29.814 --> 11:31.270
Kara.

11:33.193 --> 11:35.559
Look, three people are dead
because of you.

11:35.737 --> 11:39.571
And if someone ﬁgured out
how to control you, a lot more would die.

11:39.741 --> 11:42.198
You would be the most powerful weapon
on the planet.

11:42.369 --> 11:44.826
No one is gonna control me
any time soon.

11:46.122 --> 11:48.113
Lex didn't ﬁnd what he was looking for.

11:49.793 --> 11:52.751
You think that's gonna stop a man
like him?

11:54.714 --> 11:56.215
Get your head out of the clouds.

11:56.383 --> 12:00.217
Something's wrong with you. You need
to stay here till we ﬁgure out what it is.

12:02.514 --> 12:05.005
You can turn a blind eye...

12:05.183 --> 12:08.641
...but I'm gonna do whatever it takes
to save Earth.

12:27.664 --> 12:29.996
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

12:30.417 --> 12:32.624
I know the Daily Planet's
not half as hip...

12:32.794 --> 12:35.581
...but last I checked,
your desk is still in the bullpen.

12:35.755 --> 12:37.495
You know, across the street?

12:37.674 --> 12:40.711
Well, I doubt Lex would be thrilled
if I spilled all his secrets...

12:40.885 --> 12:44.798
...in the same place he signs my checks.
Plus, this place has an epic happy hour.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.302
Well, speaking of secrets...

12:48.476 --> 12:52.310
...I found out about those expeditions
he's been sending to the North Pole.

12:57.026 --> 12:59.517
Either he's planning a takeover
of Santa's workshop...

12:59.696 --> 13:01.277
...or doing something illegal.

13:01.448 --> 13:05.157
And since I'm sure Lex isn't into
the Christmas spirit, what's the scoop?

13:05.326 --> 13:08.659
I'm sorry to say that he's just scouting
for new places to drill oil.

13:08.830 --> 13:10.866
What? Where did you ﬁnd that out?

13:11.082 --> 13:15.121
I heard a reporter talking about it
on the third ﬂoor.

13:16.754 --> 13:17.880
Who?

13:19.674 --> 13:21.539
You know, I don't know.

13:21.718 --> 13:25.302
Ijust overheard it. I mean,
you've been up there. It's crowded.

13:25.722 --> 13:27.212
Huh.

13:30.518 --> 13:32.133
Okay.

13:32.312 --> 13:33.552
Would you just take a look?

13:33.730 --> 13:36.893
Surveyor photos
of potential drilling sites.

13:46.659 --> 13:50.527
How did Jimmy Olsen manage
to score such top-secret stuff?

13:50.705 --> 13:54.072
Lex was having them sorted
and scanned in the photo lab.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.707
I saw my opportunity and I took it.

13:57.212 --> 13:59.077
Just like you taught me.

14:02.008 --> 14:06.672
I guess I've been so focused on Lex,
I've been looking for a villain in everyone.

14:06.846 --> 14:08.507
Even you.

14:09.098 --> 14:10.087
Sorry.

14:11.601 --> 14:15.594
Look, hey, it's no big deal. Really.

14:18.107 --> 14:20.439
Got more game than I thought.

14:21.194 --> 14:22.650
Thanks.

14:38.962 --> 14:40.623
Kara?

14:42.507 --> 14:44.919
The little V with the stars...

14:45.301 --> 14:47.132
...something to do with Veritas, right?

14:49.430 --> 14:51.921
I don't know what you're talking about.

14:55.061 --> 14:58.144
Why is it that every time
I bring up Veritas...

14:58.314 --> 15:00.805
...people seem to suffer
from sudden amnesia?

15:05.947 --> 15:11.487
A secret society formed to control
a powerful alien from another planet?

15:17.667 --> 15:21.159
Veritas also means truth.

15:21.879 --> 15:24.746
So, what do you say we have some
right now?

15:24.924 --> 15:26.505
Look...

15:27.093 --> 15:28.549
...I don't know
who you've been talking to--

15:28.720 --> 15:31.257
I know about the transmissions sent
to Virgil Swann...

15:32.557 --> 15:36.345
...the ones telling him where to ﬁnd
the device to control the Traveler.

15:36.936 --> 15:38.847
How did you hear about that?

15:42.358 --> 15:44.610
The Traveler and I...

15:46.362 --> 15:48.523
...we're from the same planet.

15:53.036 --> 15:55.027
You don't believe me?

16:11.012 --> 16:12.718
The dam.

16:13.514 --> 16:15.891
You are the one who saved me.

16:17.435 --> 16:20.051
You kept denying it. Why?

16:20.521 --> 16:22.557
Why tell me now?

16:27.945 --> 16:31.608
I didn't know it then,
but I saved you for a reason, Lex.

16:32.825 --> 16:36.067
It is your destiny to defeat the Traveler.

16:37.205 --> 16:39.662
I know you have the device.

16:39.832 --> 16:42.414
And all of the pieces are in place.

16:44.045 --> 16:45.751
Now it's up to you.

16:49.092 --> 16:51.708
If you really believe I have this thing...

16:51.886 --> 16:54.252
...why don't you just take it
and do it yourself?

16:55.723 --> 16:59.432
Apparently, the orb was built
to protect the human race.

16:59.936 --> 17:02.427
So only a human can use it.

17:07.151 --> 17:09.563
It showed me a set of coordinates.

17:09.737 --> 17:11.318
Somewhere in the Arctic.

17:11.489 --> 17:13.980
Directions to his fortress.

17:14.784 --> 17:17.275
You need to take it there
to control the Traveler.

17:20.289 --> 17:24.282
Two of my advance teams, they—
They disappeared trying to get there.

17:28.881 --> 17:31.258
They didn't have a Kryptonian
to help them.

17:33.553 --> 17:37.592
You're talking about destroying
one of your own kind.

17:38.766 --> 17:41.599
I'd always thought the Traveler
was meant for good.

17:41.769 --> 17:43.475
Even he thinks he is.

17:43.646 --> 17:47.389
Then I went home to Krypton
and learned the truth about his fate.

17:49.444 --> 17:52.311
He won't save mankind...

17:52.822 --> 17:54.062
...he'll destroy it.

17:59.203 --> 18:00.909
Who is it?

18:04.500 --> 18:06.616
Don't you already know?

18:33.237 --> 18:34.738
Hey.

18:34.906 --> 18:38.865
Whoa. Breaking out the heavy artillery.

18:39.076 --> 18:43.194
It's not every day that you see Clark Kent
clutching a box of kryptonite.

18:43.372 --> 18:45.704
It's the only way to stop her.

18:46.167 --> 18:49.500
So I'm guessing face time with Kara
didn't go so well?

18:56.177 --> 18:59.635
Kara's convinced that someone will try
to use me as a weapon.

19:01.349 --> 19:04.091
She thinks I'm not doing enough
to stop it.

19:06.479 --> 19:08.265
What if she's right?

19:08.898 --> 19:13.437
Clark, Kara's a lot of things, reckless,
headstrong, possibly psychotic.

19:13.611 --> 19:15.693
But she's wrong about you.

19:15.863 --> 19:19.401
You've done everything you can
to stop Veritas and more. You know that.

19:26.791 --> 19:28.827
Obviously, she doesn't.

19:32.421 --> 19:35.003
Chloe, you're the only one
who can help me.

19:38.970 --> 19:41.052
I'm always here for you, Clark.

19:42.598 --> 19:45.806
Now, look, you—
You won't be doing it alone.

19:46.102 --> 19:48.184
We'll get her here. I'll stand by your side.

19:48.354 --> 19:52.597
Clark, if we're gonna wield this kind of
weaponry, don't shoot yourself in the foot.

19:52.775 --> 19:56.859
This little green rock will knock down
every Kryptonian in the room.

19:57.029 --> 19:59.441
You can't be around
when we lift the lid.

19:59.824 --> 20:01.610
Let me do this.

20:12.670 --> 20:14.535
The jet's fueled and waiting, sir.

20:15.131 --> 20:17.292
Tell them one more passenger is coming.

20:18.259 --> 20:19.795
Uh, where are we going?

20:20.636 --> 20:22.968
You're not going anywhere, Jimmy.

20:23.264 --> 20:26.131
Look, I know that you're busy, Lex.

20:26.309 --> 20:29.642
I just wanted you to know
that I did what you told me to do.

20:29.937 --> 20:32.474
Lois thinks you're all about the oil
up north now.

20:33.524 --> 20:35.185
Well done.

20:38.279 --> 20:40.144
So I guess, wax on, wax off.

20:40.323 --> 20:43.815
-We're even now, right?
-I believe our arrangement has just begun.

20:43.993 --> 20:46.405
I want regular reports
on Miss Lane's activities.

20:46.579 --> 20:49.321
I did what you said.
I shouldn't have to spy for you too.

20:49.498 --> 20:51.830
-That's not fair.
-Life is rarely fair.

20:52.001 --> 20:55.789
Look, Lex, I would really like to help...

20:55.963 --> 20:58.830
...but lying, it's just, you know,
it's not my thing.

20:59.008 --> 21:02.842
I mean, it's eating me up.
It actually-- It's making my stomach hurt.

21:03.012 --> 21:05.674
Well, it's never too late
to learn a new skill.

21:05.848 --> 21:07.349
Look.

21:08.976 --> 21:10.841
I'm sorry, I just--

21:13.022 --> 21:14.353
I can't do it.

21:14.857 --> 21:20.477
Trust me, I'm not gonna say a single word
to anyone about your oil drilling.

21:21.447 --> 21:23.904
Please, you gotta understand.

21:25.409 --> 21:27.274
I can't spy on my friend.

21:34.043 --> 21:36.534
I respect your integrity, Jimmy.

21:37.004 --> 21:40.872
It took a lot to come here
and lay your cards on the table.

21:44.220 --> 21:45.710
Thanks.

21:47.098 --> 21:50.431
Now if you'll step aside,
I have a plane to catch.

21:51.519 --> 21:53.009
You bet.

21:56.148 --> 21:58.230
Have a great trip, Lex.

22:07.159 --> 22:08.899
Kara, something's wrong with Clark.

22:09.078 --> 22:13.117
He's convinced that if he destroys the
Fortress, no one will be able to control him.

22:13.290 --> 22:15.827
We're at my apartment, I need your help.

22:17.086 --> 22:18.747
Where's Clark?

22:18.921 --> 22:20.912
He's right back here.

22:26.137 --> 22:27.673
Why isn't it working?

22:27.847 --> 22:29.758
Check the expiration date?

22:31.684 --> 22:33.845
Kara, something's wrong.
It was the only way--

22:34.020 --> 22:35.806
You lied to me.

22:35.980 --> 22:37.436
Clark's not here.

22:46.907 --> 22:48.443
Oh, God.

22:48.617 --> 22:50.448
I'm impressed.

22:50.619 --> 22:53.986
I wouldn't have thought a member
of your weak-willed species...

22:54.165 --> 22:59.205
...especially a friend of Kal-El's,
could ever use kryptonite against his cousin.

22:59.378 --> 23:01.164
Let me go.

23:02.465 --> 23:03.625
I remember you.

23:05.801 --> 23:11.467
Always sticking your pretty little head
where it doesn't belong.

23:18.147 --> 23:20.138
[CHLOE GRUNTING]

23:37.166 --> 23:39.498
What the hell are you?

23:47.051 --> 23:50.134
-Sir?
-Tell the pilot to start the engines.

23:51.680 --> 23:54.888
-I thought we were waiting for your guide.
-I don't need her.

23:55.059 --> 23:57.266
I'm not sure I should even trust her.

23:57.436 --> 24:00.519
But, sir, the last few teams
have all disappeared.

24:02.399 --> 24:06.233
I believe I have everything I need
to reach my destination.

24:07.363 --> 24:10.025
If this is meant to protect all humanity...

24:10.199 --> 24:13.441
-...it should protect me as well.
-But you don't know that for sure.

24:13.619 --> 24:15.120
It seems extremely dangerous.

24:16.080 --> 24:18.241
It's worth the risk.

24:19.375 --> 24:20.660
We leave now.

24:38.227 --> 24:40.218
[PLANE ENGINES WHIRRING]

25:12.261 --> 25:14.252
I'm so sorry.

25:37.453 --> 25:39.284
Brainiac.

26:00.601 --> 26:02.592
[ALARM WAILING]

27:00.077 --> 27:03.490
Kara never came back from Krypton,
did she?

27:06.792 --> 27:10.330
It was quite an impersonation, wasn't it?

27:12.548 --> 27:16.791
It was the only way I could return to Earth
without you damaging me.

27:19.054 --> 27:20.885
You killed her.

27:21.056 --> 27:24.219
Oh, no, something much worse.

27:24.393 --> 27:25.849
You'll never see her again.

27:28.981 --> 27:30.391
Where is she?

27:30.566 --> 27:31.897
I warned you.

27:32.067 --> 27:35.480
If we'd have done things my way,
no one would have gotten hurt.

27:35.654 --> 27:36.894
No one but you.

27:37.197 --> 27:39.574
So this is all about revenge?

27:40.242 --> 27:42.779
This is a simple matter
of self-preservation.

27:42.953 --> 27:46.366
When I couldn't kill you,
I knew I had to control you.

27:46.540 --> 27:48.622
I'm in control now.

27:48.792 --> 27:52.034
And you will release Chloe.
You'll release Lana.

27:52.212 --> 27:58.003
The only way to save them
would be to kill me now, in cold blood.

27:58.177 --> 28:01.260
Which goes against everything
you stand for.

28:01.513 --> 28:04.004
You could never deliberately take
another man's life.

28:05.934 --> 28:07.799
You're not a man.

28:08.312 --> 28:10.348
You're a machine.

28:16.320 --> 28:19.778
You can kill me, Kal-El...

28:20.032 --> 28:22.273
...but your end is near.

28:22.785 --> 28:25.242
And there's nothing you can do
to stop it.

28:29.416 --> 28:32.283
You'll never hurt anyone else ever again.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.244
[SCREAMING]

29:09.415 --> 29:11.371
That's great news. I'm glad you're okay.

29:11.542 --> 29:13.999
I'll call you after I check on Lana.

29:19.758 --> 29:21.339
Lana?

29:24.138 --> 29:25.674
Clark Kent?

29:26.515 --> 29:27.755
What happened?

29:27.933 --> 29:29.298
Is she okay?

29:29.476 --> 29:34.391
Miss Lang had a full recovery.
It's something of a miracle.

29:34.857 --> 29:36.688
Where is she? Can I see her?

29:36.859 --> 29:40.693
Oh, she's already checked out.
But she wanted me to give you this.

29:57.379 --> 30:01.213
l was going to wait to talk
to you in person...

30:02.718 --> 30:07.052
...but I knew that if I looked into your eyes
I'd never be able to say it.

30:12.060 --> 30:15.473
We thought that we were meant
to be together, Clark...

30:15.647 --> 30:19.981
...but the truth is,
we were fooling ourselves.

30:22.029 --> 30:23.860
I need you...

30:24.323 --> 30:25.813
...but the world needs you more.

30:26.533 --> 30:30.902
And as long as I'm in your life,
I am holding you back.

30:33.081 --> 30:36.244
Please, don 't come after me.

30:44.343 --> 30:46.049
[love you, Clark.

30:53.268 --> 30:55.600
More than you will ever know.

31:25.217 --> 31:26.957
I'm so sorry.

31:53.662 --> 31:57.325
You just got out of the hospital, Chloe,
so take it slow, okay?

31:57.499 --> 32:00.081
You know what, maybe I should—
I'll carry you upstairs.

32:00.252 --> 32:02.459
Jimmy, we're climbing the stairs
to the Talon...

32:02.629 --> 32:05.211
...not scaling the mountains of Tibet.
I'm ﬁne.

32:05.382 --> 32:08.670
How about some water? Or tea?
I've pretty much mastered the tai chi--

32:11.138 --> 32:13.174
Maybe you're not supposed
to have caffeine.

32:13.348 --> 32:17.591
So maybe I should just get you some--
Some bottled water or some tap water.

32:19.521 --> 32:21.512
I know, some sparkling...

32:21.857 --> 32:24.189
...because, you know,
it matches your smile.

32:25.360 --> 32:28.102
Jimmy, I realize that I was the one
that was in the ICU...

32:28.280 --> 32:32.865
...but you seem to be the one
with marred motor skills. Are you okay?

32:34.411 --> 32:35.947
Yeah.

32:37.831 --> 32:39.367
Okay.

32:41.376 --> 32:42.877
Chloe.

32:48.759 --> 32:50.875
Look, until tonight...

32:51.637 --> 32:53.548
...I never thought that I would lose you.

32:54.473 --> 32:59.888
I mean, I know that we've been, you know,
on again and off again and on again.

33:00.604 --> 33:01.719
But...

33:03.440 --> 33:06.352
...I ﬁgured,
even if we didn't end up together...

33:07.861 --> 33:10.648
...I could be happy
just knowing that you're in the world.

33:14.117 --> 33:15.903
But today...

33:17.537 --> 33:19.823
...I realized that that's not true.

33:21.833 --> 33:27.703
No, I mean, of course I'm happy
that you're in the world.

33:30.217 --> 33:32.959
But you mean so much to me, Chloe.

33:36.598 --> 33:38.759
And I want to spend the rest of our time
in it together.

33:53.573 --> 33:56.280
It's all they had
at the hospital gift shop...

33:57.285 --> 33:59.116
...but I didn't wanna wait.

33:59.788 --> 34:02.621
We can have Breakfast at Tiffany's
in the morning.

34:07.295 --> 34:09.126
Will you marry me?

34:09.631 --> 34:10.962
AGENT 1:
Don't move!

34:11.508 --> 34:15.126
-Hey, hold on. This isn't right.
CHLOE: What's going on?

34:15.303 --> 34:18.045
Hey, who do you guys think you are?

34:18.223 --> 34:20.305
AGENT 2: Department of Domestic Security.
-Jimmy.

34:20.475 --> 34:22.306
AGENT 2:
Chloe Sullivan, you're under arrest.

34:22.477 --> 34:23.592
Jimmy, call Clark.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.306
Get Clark!

34:25.480 --> 34:27.471
[GRUNTING]

34:35.490 --> 34:36.821
[CLATTERING]

34:36.992 --> 34:38.573
JIMMY:
Clark!

34:39.077 --> 34:41.113
Clark, are you here?

34:41.872 --> 34:43.453
Clark!

34:45.917 --> 34:49.159
Clark, Chloe was just arrested.

34:49.546 --> 34:51.002
What?

34:51.173 --> 34:54.336
Her habitual hacking
caught Uncle Sam's eye. So I—

34:55.844 --> 34:58.051
I went to Lex for help.
Now he's holding it over me.

34:58.221 --> 35:00.177
You made a deal with Lex Luthor?

35:00.348 --> 35:02.964
I told him to get another lap dog, Clark.

35:03.143 --> 35:04.553
But then he just—

35:04.728 --> 35:07.390
He put her back
on their "most wanted" list.

35:08.482 --> 35:12.145
She went from life support
to life without parole in less than a day.

35:12.319 --> 35:14.150
-Where's Lex now?
-Look, I don't know.

35:14.321 --> 35:17.529
I tried to contact him, but he's off
jet-setting around the Arctic Circle.

35:17.699 --> 35:19.030
It's not drilling oil...

35:19.201 --> 35:22.193
...because he's gone way out of his way
to cover his tracks.

37:18.153 --> 37:20.269
I must admit, Clark...

37:21.031 --> 37:23.773
...this is a big step up from the barn.

37:24.034 --> 37:26.320
It's not what you think, Lex.

37:27.329 --> 37:29.320
You don't understand.

37:36.588 --> 37:39.000
For the ﬁrst time, I think I do.

37:40.175 --> 37:44.168
You see, you live among us
as a mild-mannered farm boy.

37:44.763 --> 37:48.676
But secretly you're a strange visitor
from another planet, plotting our demise.

37:48.850 --> 37:52.684
-That's not what I'm doing at all.
-lt's a brilliant disguise, Clark.

37:53.188 --> 37:54.678
You don't even need a mask.

37:56.524 --> 37:58.560
I'm not your enemy, Lex.

37:59.027 --> 38:01.359
I've never done anything to hurt you.

38:02.405 --> 38:04.361
You didn't trust me.

38:05.200 --> 38:08.237
With everything you had,
with everything you could do...

38:08.411 --> 38:11.869
...did you ever think about
what we could have accomplished together?

38:12.165 --> 38:14.156
I would have helped you become a hero.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.866
When have you thought
of anyone but yourself?

38:17.045 --> 38:18.660
Right now.

38:18.838 --> 38:20.874
I'm doing this for the world.

38:21.049 --> 38:23.540
I have to protect the human race.

38:23.718 --> 38:25.003
This is my life.

38:25.178 --> 38:28.716
-You have no right to control it.
-lt's my birthright.

38:28.890 --> 38:33.224
After all my sacriﬁces,
after all the pain...

38:33.395 --> 38:35.636
...I ﬁnally understand.

38:35.897 --> 38:40.106
I was being prepared
for a much greater destiny.

38:40.610 --> 38:43.067
Everything led me to this moment.

38:43.238 --> 38:44.523
And we're both here.

38:44.698 --> 38:46.279
We're in that moment.

38:46.449 --> 38:49.236
And what happens next is your choice.

38:49.661 --> 38:51.617
But no one is controlling you, Lex.

38:51.788 --> 38:54.074
No one is forcing you to do this.

38:54.708 --> 38:57.745
LEX: Who am I to turn my back
on my fellow man...

38:57.919 --> 39:00.831
...especially after you
turned your back on me?

39:03.633 --> 39:05.464
I'm sorry, Clark...

39:05.635 --> 39:08.092
...but you are the Traveler.

39:16.438 --> 39:17.848
I'm here to take it back.

39:18.023 --> 39:19.684
Lex.

39:20.567 --> 39:23.274
You'll never threaten the world again...

39:23.611 --> 39:24.771
...Kal-El.

39:27.282 --> 39:28.863
Lex, don't!

39:38.293 --> 39:40.284
[RUMBLING]

39:54.809 --> 39:57.551
I love you like a brother, Clark...

39:57.729 --> 39:59.640
...but it has to end this way.

40:06.488 --> 40:08.274
I'm
sorry

41:13.763 --> 41:15.754
[ENGLISH SDH]
